## Pacing/Cut Suggestions

1. **Hard-cut on the beat drop, not on the VO gap** — since counters `1/5`→`5/5` land back-to-back every ~6s, sync the cut point to the music kick rather than the exact VO boundary; a half-beat-early cut (~150–200ms before "สอง", "สาม"...) reads as snappier and hides the audio-splice better than cutting exactly at word onset.
2. **Speed-ramp the tool-screen B-roll** — for beats 1–3 (Script/Caption/Thumbnail), fast-forward the app-recording footage 1.5–2x during the "typing/generating" moments and cut back to real-time exactly when the AI output appears on screen; this reinforces the "time saved" premise visually instead of just via the on-screen timer text, and keeps those three beats feeling shorter than the Edit (CapCut) beat, which should stay closer to real-time since it's the biggest time-save claim (1-2hr → 20-30min) and needs to feel *substantial*, not rushed.